window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Spot and his loyal followers have defended their castle from danger. However, there is no time to rest.</b></p> <p>With home safe and the Kingdom's army swept away, they must press forward if they want to secure their future, even if it means war.</p> <p>Accompanied by their friends and allies, Spot and Beatrice head to the Kingdom's capital to sort out this tangled situation. But armed conflict won't be their only worry. There are also the matters of family, and a strange new cult has attracted a great deal of attention.</p> <p>As Spot continues to tidy up every messy situation they encounter, he and his people will find themselves embroiled in power struggles and unexpectedly tangled plots far deeper than they could have expected. Ones with potentially world-ending consequences …</p> <p>Luckily, his influence can reach even the tightest and dirtiest of corners.</p> <p><b>This tale of a wholesome vacuum on his quest to power comes to its epic conclusion in </b><b><i>All the Dust that Falls 4</i></b><b>, a hilarious Isekai LitRPG that will make you question what it means to be a hero. Or if heroes even need limbs, or mouths, or … you get it.</b></p>"; 
